                                                                <customfield id="customfield_12310192" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Release Note</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>&amp;nbsp;An EvalFunc can annotated with an @OutputSchema annotation to&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;tell Pig what the expected output is. This can be used in place&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;of EvalFunc.outputSchema(Schema inpSchema)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The default implementation of EvalFunc.outputSchema(Schema inpSchema) will look at this annotation and return an interpreted schema, if the annotation is present.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Implementing a custom EvalFunc.outputSchema(Schema inpSchema) will override the annotation (unless you deal with it explicitly, or by calling super.outputSchema(schema))&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Here&amp;#39;s an example of a complex schema declared in an annotation:&lt;br/&gt;
@OutputSchema(&amp;quot;y:bag{t:tuple(len:int,word:chararray)}&amp;quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
</customfieldvalue>

                        </customfieldvalues>
